EDA

Introduction

Our task is to explore the data and prepare a 1/2 to 1 page written overview of our findings.

About the data:

The NTSB aviation accident database contains information from 1962 and later about civil aviation accidents and selected incidents within the United States, its territories and possessions, and in international waters. Generally, a preliminary report is available online within a few days of an accident. Factual information is added when available, and when the investigation is completed, the preliminary report is replaced with a final description of the accident and its probable cause. Full narrative descriptions may not be available for dates before 1993, cases under revision, or where NTSB did not have primary investigative responsibility.

Exploratory Data Analysis

library(XML)
library(tidyverse)

theme_set(theme_minimal()) # set the ggplot theme

Load the data

# parse the xml file
data <- xmlParse("data/AviationData.xml")

# put all child nodes of the root node into a list
xml_data <- xmlToList(data)

# convert the list into a dataframe
df <- data.frame(matrix(unlist(xml_data$ROWS), nrow=length(xml_data$ROWS), byrow=TRUE))

Clean the data

# column names (can be found by inspecting the xml file)
colnames(df) <- c("EventID", "InvestigationType", "AccidentNumber", "EventDate", "Location", "Country", "Latitude", "Longitude", "AirportCode", "AirportName", "InjurySeverity", "AircraftDamage", "AircraftCategory", "RegistrationNumber", "Make", "Model", "AmateurBuilt", "NumberOfEngines", "EngineType", "FARDescription", "Schedule", "PurposeOfFlight", "AirCarrier", "TotalFatalInjuries", "TotalSeriousInjuries", "TotalMinorInjuries", "TotalUninjured", "WeatherCondition", "BroadPhaseOfFlight", "ReportStatus", "PublicationDate")
# convert missing data to NA
df <- df %>% replace_with_na(replace = list(x = ""))

# time series plot
tmp <- df %>%
  filter(InvestigationType == "Accident") %>% # remove incidents, which are always non-fatal
  mutate(InjuryType = ifelse(InjurySeverity %in% c("Non-Fatal", "Unavailable"), as.character(InjurySeverity), "Fatal")) %>%
  filter(!(InjuryType %in% c("Unavailable"))) %>% # remove missing values
  select(EventDate, InjuryType) %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  mutate(EventDate = mdy(EventDate),
         Year = year(EventDate)) %>%
  group_by(InjuryType, Year) %>%
  summarise(n = n())

# Plot accidents over time 
ggplot(tmp,aes(Year, n, color=InjuryType)) + 
  geom_line() +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(1982, 2016), breaks = seq(1982, 2015, 1)) + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90)) 

tmp <- df %>%
  select(EventDate) %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  mutate(EventDate = mdy(EventDate),
         Month = month(EventDate)) %>%
  group_by(Month) %>%
  summarise(n = n()) %>%
  mutate(freq = n/(sum(n)))
`summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
# Since we notice a seasonal cycle, investigate the months
ggplot(tmp, aes(Month, freq)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels=scales::percent) +
  ylab("Relative frequencies") +
  scale_x_continuous(limits=c(0,13), breaks = seq(1,12,1)) +
  ggtitle("Accidents by month")

Insights: Accidents happen in the summer months. They are decreasing over time.

# airport code
tmp <- df %>%
  filter(InvestigationType == "Accident") %>% # remove incidents, which are always non-fatal
  mutate(InjuryType = ifelse(InjurySeverity %in% c("Incident", "Non-Fatal", "Unavailable"), as.character(InjurySeverity), "Fatal")) %>%
  filter(!(InjuryType %in% c("Unavailable"))) %>% # remove undefined values
  select(AirportName, AircraftCategory, InjuryType) %>%
  mutate(AirportName = toupper(AirportName)) %>%
  mutate(AirportName = ifelse(grepl("PRIVATE", AirportName, fixed = T)==T, "PRIVATE", as.character(AirportName))) %>%
  mutate(AirportName = na_if(AirportName, "N/A")) %>%
  mutate(AirportName = na_if(AirportName, "NONE")) %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  group_by(InjuryType, AirportName) %>%
  summarise(n = n()) %>%
  mutate(Freq = n / sum(n)) %>%
  top_n(n=3)

ggplot(tmp, aes(x=reorder(AirportName,n), y=n)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  ylab("Count") +
  xlab("Make") +
  coord_flip() +
  facet_wrap(vars(InjuryType), scale = "free") +
  ggtitle("Airports with the most accidents")

tmp <- df %>%

# plot
ggplot(tmp, aes(x=InjuryType, fill=InjuryType)) + 
  geom_bar(aes(y = (..count..)/sum(..count..))) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels=scales::percent) +
  ylab("Relative frequencies") +
  theme(axis.title.x=element_blank(),
        axis.text.x=element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.x=element_blank()) +
  ggtitle("Types of Accidents")
# If fatal, how many people died?
tmp <- tmp %>% 
  filter(InjuryType %in% "Fatal") %>%
  mutate(Deaths = as.numeric(unlist(str_extract_all(InjurySeverity, "(?<=\\().+?(?=\\))"))))
  
# plot all fatalities. y-axis is sqrt transformation to show outliers
ggplot(tmp, aes(x=Deaths)) + 
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1) +
  scale_y_sqrt() +
  ggtitle("All fatalities")

# plot accidents with 1-10 fatalities
ggplot(tmp, aes(Deaths)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "count") +
  scale_x_continuous(limits=c(0,11), breaks = seq(1,10,1)) +
  ggtitle("Fatalities between 1-10")

Insights: Most accidents are non-fatal. Fatal accidents generally involve 5 or fewer deaths.

tmp <- df %>%
  filter(InvestigationType == "Accident") %>% # remove incidents, which are always non-fatal
  mutate(InjuryType = ifelse(InjurySeverity %in% c("Incident", "Non-Fatal", "Unavailable"), as.character(InjurySeverity), "Fatal")) %>%
  filter(!(InjuryType %in% c("Unavailable"))) %>% # remove undefined values
  select(Make, AircraftCategory, InjuryType) %>%
  filter(AircraftCategory %in% c("Airplane", "Helicopter")) %>%
  drop_na() %>%
  mutate(Make = ifelse(grepl("ROBINSON", Make, fixed = T)==T, "ROBINSON", as.character(Make))) %>% # consolidate duplicate names

  group_by(InjuryType, AircraftCategory, Make) %>%
  summarise(n = n()) %>%
  mutate(Freq = n / sum(n)) %>%
  top_n(n=5)

  xlab("Make") +
  coord_flip() +

# Identify the top airplane and helicoptor companties associated with accidents 

tmp <- df %>%
  filter(InvestigationType == "Accident") %>% # remove incidents, which are always non-fatal
  mutate(InjuryType = ifelse(InjurySeverity %in% c("Incident", "Non-Fatal", "Unavailable"), as.character(InjurySeverity), "Fatal")) %>%

# air carrier
remove <- c("\\*|\\(|\\)", ".*:", "INC", "LTD", ",", "\\.", "\\[|\\]", "EMS") # list of expressions to remove

tmp <- df %>%
  mutate(AirCarrier = toupper(as.character(AirCarrier))) %>%
  mutate(AirCarrier = str_remove_all(AirCarrier, paste(remove, collapse = "|"))) %>%
  mutate(AirCarrier = str_trim(AirCarrier, side = "both")) %>%
  mutate(AirCarrier = str_replace(AirCarrier, "AIR LINES", "AIRLINES")) %>%
  filter(!(AirCarrier %in% c(""))) %>%
  drop_na(AirCarrier) %>%
  group_by(InvestigationType, AirCarrier) %>%
  summarise(count=n()) %>%
  top_n(n=10)

Selecting by count

# time-series of each injury type
tmp <- df %>%
  mutate_at(vars(TotalFatalInjuries, TotalSeriousInjuries, TotalMinorInjuries, TotalUninjured), ~as.numeric(as.character(.))) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("Total"), names_to = "Severity", values_to = "Individuals") %>%
  mutate(Severity = str_remove(Severity, "Total")) %>%
  mutate(EventDate = lubridate::mdy(EventDate)) %>%
  mutate(Year = lubridate::year(EventDate)) %>%
  group_by(Year, Severity) %>%
  summarise(n = sum(Individuals, na.rm = T))
  
# Plot injuries over time 
ggplot(tmp,aes(x=Year, y=n, color=Severity)) + 
  geom_line() +
  xlim(c(1982, 2015)) +
  
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90))
